            <p class="eyebrow">Why maintenance matters</p>
            <h2>What happens when drain systems are neglected</h2>
            <p>Without regular maintenance, drain and sewer systems deteriorate and create increasingly serious problems.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Clogs and slow drainage</h3><p>Accumulated buildup from grease, soap, hair, and other debris gradually restricts flow until drains stop working entirely.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Foul odors</h3><p>Organic matter decomposing inside neglected drain lines creates persistent, unpleasant smells throughout the home.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Sewer backups</h3><p>Neglected sewer lines can back up into your home, creating health hazards and causing significant property damage.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>04</span><div><h3>Costly repairs</h3><p>Small problems left unchecked become cracked or collapsed lines that require expensive emergency repair or replacement.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>05</span><div><h3>Reduced system longevity</h3><p>Without proper maintenance, drain and sewer systems wear out years before they should, leading to premature replacement costs.</p></div></article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

