            <h2>Why professional service matters</h2>
            <p>Store-bought chemicals and DIY approaches often do more harm than good.</p>
            <ul class="check-list">
              <li>Store-bought chemicals leave residue and can corrode pipes over time</li>
              <li>Improper tools damage pipes and push clogs deeper into the system</li>
              <li>Amateur efforts miss underlying issues that require professional diagnosis</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Professional drain maintenance uses the right tools for each situation and identifies problems before they become emergencies.</p>
